snippet.textDisplay:
What impresses me is the Company HYBE. When they were on the brink of bankruptcy to where they are now. The sets they have come up with had to be built. The giant disco ball with all the lights computerized, the ramp, the dance floor. The stage settings for the Official Butter MV. The sets they built for the live shows on the Late Show, the locations on and Home set on the Late NIght Show with Jimmy Fallon, the rooms in the Life goes On/Dynamite and the stage set of the Late Late Show with James Corden.
They really make sure that the BTS members look great in whatever they do, costumes, settings, detail.

snippet.textDisplay: Really close inspection, there are very slight clues that they are really singing. A few pops, a missed queue where a pre-recorded backup vocal says "oooo". If this wasn't processed after the recording then that is fantastic singing. Not a single mistake, instant hitting the note, no volume drop out, totally in tune. To do that while dancing, and maintain that degree of precision is well, I don't know how hard that is for pros, but whatever it is, these guys have it.
